trend_summary: A compact grid persists, but scattered vacant lots and old warehouses are steadily replaced by larger multi-storey blocks, mainly in the south. Industrial land contracts, commercial and institutional roofs expand, and street-side tree canopy and park greenery increase. Sports fields are modernised. The area consolidates as a mature, densely built urban core.
notable_changes: Vacant parcels converted to new multi-storey buildings, boosting floor area in the south-central zone.
Several ageing industrial roofs replaced by brighter, larger commercial or tech facilities near the rail corridor.
Street trees and landscaped medians broaden, increasing vegetative cover along major avenues and around the lake.
Athletic track and adjacent stadium receive resurfacing and new ancillary structures, indicating facility upgrades.
